Genomics Lab Data

Source: R/gendata.R
gendata.Rd

This dataset comes from analysed RNAseq data and has been adjusted and edited to not conflict with copyright of the lab. It contains the following parameter values for 8651 genes.

gendata

Format

A data frame with 8651 rows and 9 variables:

gene

character. gene names

sample_1

character. description of trial in this case this was the control

sample_2

character. description of trial in this case the experiment (change in independent variable)

value_1

double. expression levels of the gene in control trial

value_2

double. expression levels of gene in experimental trial

log2.fold_change.

double. values of the change in expression usually calculated using the log2 of the experiment divided by the control

p_value

double. p-value of whether the change in expression level is significant

q_value

double. adjusted p-value for the false discovery rate (FDR)

significant

character. yes/no indicating significant/non-significant change in expression
